SECTION 1. Section 4 of Republic Act. No. 8048, also known as the 芒聙聹Coconut Preservation Act of 1995?, is hereby amended to read as follows:

芒聙聹SEC. 4.

Prohibition.

芒聙聯 No coconut tree shall be cut except in the following cases and only after a permit had been issued therefor:

芒聙聹(a) When the tree is sixty (60) years old in the case of tall varieties, and at least forty (40) years old for dwarf varieties;

芒聙聹(b) When the tree is no longer economically productive;

芒聙聹(c) When the tree is severely disease-infested and beyond rehabilitation;

芒聙聹(d) When the tree is severely damaged by typhoon or lightning;

芒聙聹(e) When the agricultural land devoted to coconut production shall have been converted in accordance with law into residential, commercial or industrial areas;

芒聙聹(f) When the land devoted to coconut production shall be converted into other agricultural uses or other agriculture-related activities in pursuance to a conversion duly applied for by the owner and approved by the proper authorities:

Provided,

SEC. 3. A new Section 7 is hereby inserted after Section 6 of this Act, to read as follows:

芒聙聹SEC. 7.

Police Powers.

芒聙聯 The PCA shall be vested with the authority to exercise duly delegated police powers for the proper performance of its functions and duties, to wit:

芒聙聹(a) Investigate suspected violations of this Act;

芒聙聹(b) Arrest and apprehend any person actually committing or attempting to commit an offense under this Act;

芒聙聹(c) Arrest and apprehend possessor of coconut lumber without the necessary permit as required under this Act;

芒聙聹(d) Search and seize a moving vehicle with illegally cut, gathered, collected or removed coconut lumber:

Provided,

That probable cause for the search is established;

芒聙聹(e) Stop the transport and/or shipment of coconut lumber without authority or without legal documents in accordance with pertinent laws, regulations or policies on the matter;
